{"ts":"2026-07-11T03:00:06.909Z","author":"maintainer-agent","op":"create","patch":[{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/id","value":"pm-eqk0"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/title","value":"pm next / claim --next treat human-gated Decision items as claimable agent work — agent lanes can claim ADRs they must never resolve"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/description","value":"Observed 2026-07-11: pm next recommends pm-pbyu (type Decision, ADR status proposed, priority 1) as THE recommended item, and pm claim --next would atomically claim it. ADR acceptance is a maintainer-only act (project convention: agents never flip ADRs), so an autonomous agent following the recommend-claim loop lands on an item it cannot resolve — a stalled lane, and at fleet scale every idle agent funnels into the same unresolvable Decision. The recommendation itself is informative (pm-pbyu + pm-bl8x gate 13 of 25 blocked items), so the fix is presentation + claim semantics, not ranking: Decisions belong in a decision-needed channel that names what they unblock, while the claimable recommendation stays actionable-by-agents. Complements closed pm-9x6k (dependency actionability) and pm-114v (atomic claim --next)."},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/type","value":"Issue"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/status","value":"open"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/priority","value":2},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/tags","value":["decisions","multi-agent","next","workflow"]},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/created_at","value":"2026-07-11T03:00:06.909Z"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/updated_at","value":"2026-07-11T03:00:06.909Z"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/author","value":"maintainer-agent"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/estimated_minutes","value":90},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/acceptance_criteria","value":"pm next surfaces open Decision-type items in a distinct decision-needed section (with what they gate) instead of as the claimable recommendation; pm claim --next skips Decision-type items unless an explicit opt-in flag is passed; behavior documented and covered by tests; existing recommendation ranking otherwise unchanged"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/risk","value":"medium"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/confidence","value":"medium"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/dependencies","value":[{"id":"pm-114v","kind":"related","created_at":"2026-07-11T03:00:06.909Z"},{"id":"pm-9x6k","kind":"related","created_at":"2026-07-11T03:00:06.909Z"}]}],"before_hash":"3cc22dff72be7b14824654a7a64ea62b04799939b2fee54c1b5f52ca60bf6df0","after_hash":"407b09b8421b28541db82a5e8089f1698799a5c915648e6ca70a99a9e320f31a","message":""}
{"ts":"2026-07-11T03:06:49.579Z","author":"maintainer-agent","op":"comment_add","patch":[{"op":"replace","path":"/metadata/updated_at","value":"2026-07-11T03:06:49.579Z"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/comments","value":[{"created_at":"2026-07-11T03:06:49.578Z","author":"maintainer-agent","text":"External confirmation (2026-07-11): GH-509 (pm-fjxm) independently requests the fleet worker loop this item protects — bounded candidate-walk on claim race loss. A walk WITHOUT the Decision-skip this item specifies makes the hazard strictly worse: every race loser advances down the ready queue and lands on the Decision item, so the funnel-into-one-ADR failure becomes the common path, not the unlucky one. pm-fjxm's AC references this item; sequencing preference: land eqk0's Decision-skip before or with fjxm's walk."}]}],"before_hash":"407b09b8421b28541db82a5e8089f1698799a5c915648e6ca70a99a9e320f31a","after_hash":"76fd29b3ef8db05077d86868a9a8d8a35393e8891801531f936f444d59403f6f"}
